author: COMSOL
description:
In this example, wrinkling is studied in a nonuniform thick membrane made of an incompressible Mooney–Rivlin material. Certain portion of the membrane undergoes wrinkling when prestretched and inflated, which disappears depending on the internal pressure.

The results of the deformation gradient approach is compared with the results of the relaxed strain energy approach.
label: membrane_varying_thickness.mph
